      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how much you've given, and I understand why the idea of \"finding new meaning\" feels like a cruel lie when your battery is truly dead. It is okay to stop trying to perform if there is nothing left to give; the pressure to be someone else is a heavy burden that no one should have to carry alone. Please consider that there are people who can help you navigate this transition and find new meaning, as your worth extends far beyond this project. If you feel overwhelmed, reaching out to a mental health professional or a crisis line can provide the support you need right now.",
